A Polistes aurifer is a species of paper wasp found in Central and South America.
Its body is dark brown or black in color with yellow or golden markings.
The abdomen is long and slender with a narrow waist, giving it a characteristic wasp-like appearance.
Its wings are translucent with dark veins running through them.
The head of Polistes aurifer has two prominent compound eyes and two large antennae.
The species is commonly found in open fields, forests, and gardens, where they build their nests using wood fibers and saliva.
Polistes aurifer is known for its aggressive behavior and painful sting, making it a formidable insect to encounter.
